ing engagements and personal giving page; transparent about donor impact", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "The Foursquare Church (International)", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "foursquare.org", "city": "Los Angeles", "state": "CA", "summary": "International Pentecostal denomination with thousands of affiliated churches and missionaries globally. Established giving platform and donor programs supporting international missions and local ministry.", "fit_score": 9, "fit_reason": "Documented donor support programs, missionary giving pages, and established fundraising infrastructure for global ministry network", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "The Gospel Coalition", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "thegospelcoalition.org", "city": "Chicago", "state": "IL", "summary": "Scholarly Christian ministry publishing theological content, reform theology resources, and academic Christian teaching. Focuses on equipping pastors and Christians with biblical scholarship.", "fit_score": 9, "fit_reason": "Clearly visible giving/donate button on website, active fundraising messaging, published prayer letters, ministry seeks ongoing donor support", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "The Navigators", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "navigators.org/giving", "city": "Colorado Springs", "state": "CO", "summary": "International Christian mentoring and discipleship ministry with strong intergenerational mentoring programs connecting older believers with younger generations. Active in campus, military, and community-based mentorship.", "fit_score": 9, "fit_reason": "Established giving platform with prayer letter updates, explicit focus on intergenerational discipleship and mentoring relationships, large scale fundraising operations", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "The Navigators - College Ministry", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "navigators.org", "city": "Colorado Springs", "state": "CO", "summary": "Scripture memory and discipleship-focused Christian ministry on college campuses nationally. College ministry directors actively seek financial partners for campus outreach.", "fit_score": 9, "fit_reason": "Documented personal support pages for college staff, prayer letter circulation model, visible expansion into new campuses", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "The Orthodox Church in America", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "oca.org", "city": "Syosset", "state": "NY", "summary": "Autocephalous Orthodox Christian church with 700+ parishes across North America. Focuses on evangelism, education, and pastoral care in Orthodox tradition.", "fit_score": 9, "fit_reason": "Established fundraising infrastructure with parish giving pages, annual giving campaigns, and documented capital projects seeking donor support", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "The Preschool at Peachtree Road United Methodist Church", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "thepreschool.org", "city": "Atlanta", "state": "GA", "summary": "501(c)(3) faith-based preschool for ages 12 months through 6 years. Operating dual annual fund campaigns: ''Grow With Me'' for teacher support and programs, and ''All In For Our Kids'' for comprehensive school support.", "fit_score": 9, "fit_reason": "Established annual giving programs with documented fundraising campaigns. 501(c)(3) nonprofit status. Clear director leadership structure. Active solicitation of donor support through formal annual fund.", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Through the Roof", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "throughtheroof.org", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "UK-registered charity (since 1997) dedicated to transforming lives through Jesus with disabled people. Uses ABC framework (Access, Belonging, Commission) to train churches on disability inclusion. The Roofbreaker Project has equipped 1,000+ churches to become more inclusive. Partners with Joni and Friends.", "fit_score": 9, "fit_reason": "Established disability inclusion ministry with clear fundraising strategy, transparent donation system through JustGiving, 27-year track record, documented milestone achievements (1000th Roofbreaker celebration 2025), international reach with structured training programs for churches.", "source_query": "Through the Roof ministry disability inclusion fundraising", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Trinity Broadcasting Network (TBN)", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "tbn.org", "city": "Irving", "state": "TX", "summary": "Global Christian broadcaster with television, radio, and digital platforms; operates international ministry centers with organized donor support structures", "fit_score": 9, "fit_reason": "Large-scale Christian media organization with documented fundraising platform, ministry partner programs, and organized donation channels", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Trinity Evangelical Divinity School (TEDS)", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "www.tiu.edu/divinity", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Evangelical seminary offering MA and PhD in Intercultural Studies. Mission and Evangelism Department with faculty including Harold A. Netland and David M. Gustafson (Department Chair). Courses in contextualization, missiology, philosophy of religion, and cultural exegesis.", "fit_score": 9, "fit_reason": "Dedicated missiology department with named faculty leadership, graduate-level training in intercultural studies, established donor base for seminary operations", "source_query": "Trinity Evangelical Divinity School missiology program faculty", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}]'::jsonb)
  as x(org_name text, org_type text, website text, city text, state text,
       summary text, fit_score int, fit_reason text, source_query text, meta jsonb)),
-- Count how many existing rows (queue + pipeline) share each URL.
-- A URL on exactly one row is a person-specific page safe to dedup
-- against; a URL shared by many is a roster/platform page and must
-- NOT cause a skip, or we'd drop distinct people who list it.
existing_sites as (
  select site, count(*) as n from (
    select rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/') as site
      from sales.scout_candidates where website is not null and btrim(website) <> ''
    union all
    select rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/') as site
      from sales.leads where website is not null and btrim(website) <> ''
  ) w group by site)
insert into sales.scout_candidates
  (org_name, org_type, website, city, state, summary,
   fit_score, fit_reason, source_query, status, meta)
select s.org_name, s.org_type, s.website, s.city, s.state, s.summary,
       s.fit_score, s.fit_reason, s.source_query, 'pending', coalesce(s.meta, '{}'::jsonb)
from src s
where not exists (select 1 from sales.scout_candidates c
                  where lower(trim(c.org_name)) = lower(trim(s.org_name)))
  and not exists (select 1 from sales.leads l
                  where lower(trim(l.org_name)) = lower(trim(s.org_name)))
  and not exists (select 1 from existing_sites es
                  where s.website is not null and btrim(s.website) <> ''
                    and es.n = 1
                    and es.site = rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(s.website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/'));